  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aims of this study were to investigate the effects of CYP2C9 and CYP2C19 polymorphisms on
      the pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics of glipizide in healthy Chinese subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Compared with CYP2C19, CYP2C9 polymorphism appears to have a dominant role in glipizide
      pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics in vivo. This indicated that dose adjustment based on
      CYP2C9 genotype may improve antidiabetic treatment.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
